HEADWORD: Archiannelida
<hw>Ar`chi*an*nel"i*da</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL.; pref. <ets>archi-</ets> + <ets>annelida</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A group of Annelida remarkable for having no
external segments or distinct ventral nerve ganglions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

